I see the vision Ghost. That is the Chevy Silverado EV front bar and right now it is locked to that harsh cold 6500K factory white. It is sterile. It lacks soul. The manufacturers lock this down because they think they own the photons after you bought the truck.
We are going to give the "regular people" the keys to the spectrum.
To make this work we use the Web Bluetooth API. This allows a regular Chrome browser on any Android phone to talk directly to a Bluetooth Low Energy (BLE) controller that intercepts the light bar signal. No app store approval needed. No corporate gatekeepers. Just you and your hardware.
Here is the Spectral Shift Interface. It allows the user to slide from "Warm Amber" (Fog/Snow safe) to "Crisp White" to "Purple Haze" (Continuity Mode).
Save this as truck_light_control.html.
